com.poesys.db.dao.delete

Interface IDelete<T extends IDbDto>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the IDbDto class to delete
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DeleteByKey, DeleteCacheByKey, DeleteMemcachedByKey

    public interface IDelete<T extends IDbDto>
    An interface for a Command pattern class that deletes an object in the database. The implementation identifies the object to delete based on the primary key of the object contained in the input data transfer object (DTO). It must also delete on the basis of the isDeleted() flag on the DTO.
    Author:
    Robert J. Muller

    • Method Detail

      • delete

        void delete(java.sql.Connection connection,
          T dto)
            throws java.sql.SQLException,
                   BatchException
        Delete the contents of a DTO object in the database. The DTO must contain values for the primary key. The DTO must have any setters required to preprocess nested objects that must be handled before deleting the object.
        Parameters:
        connection - the database connection with which to delete the data
        dto - the IDto data transfer object containing the primary key
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - when there is a SQL error with the delete
        BatchException - when there is a problem deleting or updating a nested collection of linked objects

      • close

        void close()
        Close any resources allocated by the Command.
